article.headline: Austin Peay 52, St. Louis 45 (OT)
article.story: CHARLOTTE AMALIE, U.S. Virgin Islands (AP) -- Maurice Hampton made a tying 3-pointer with two seconds left in regulation and Austin Peay hung on in overtime to beat Saint Louis 52-45 Friday night in the first game of the Paradise Jam tournament. Saint Louis trailed the entire game before point guard Dwayne Polk capped a late surge with a breakaway finger roll that gave the Billikens their first lead with two minutes left. Levi Carmichael hit a clutch 3-pointer then one of two free throws to give Austin Peay a 50-45 lead with a minute left in overtime. St. Louis made just 26 percent of its field goals and 18 percent from 3-point range. The Billikens were unable to capitalize on 17 Austin Peay turnovers.
